6 telephone number and electronic mail address for each such
7 representative;
8 2. A description and a map or plat for any proposed electric
9 transmission facility route or alternative route, regardless of
10 whether a transmission developer has made a submission or received
11 approval from the Southwest Power Pool or any other applicable
12 regional planning process or other federal authority, or made no
13 submission or received approval from any such entities;
14 3. Identification of any and all such counties within any
15 proposed electric transmission facility route or alternative route;
16 and
17 4. Identification of any energy resource to which the electric
18 transmission facility is to be directly connected or, to the extent
19 known, resources to which the electric transmission facility could
20 be connected to integrate existing natural gas or other resource
21 generation.
